post5.caption: Chasing hot air balloons and desert skies 🏜🎈. Spent the last week exploring Phoenix, AZ and man was it hot 🥵. Some days reaching almost 118 degrees! Sunrise definitely became my favorite time of day because that was when it was only 90 degrees 😂. Seeing these balloons float over the Sonoran Desert was definitely worth the 3am wake up call ✨ @visitphoenix @hotairexpeditions

post6.caption: Have spent the past 2 days exploring Sedona with @polarisadventures for National Get Outside Day. It was so nice to disconnect with my phone and reconnect with nature ✨. Saw so many amazing places and beautiful red rocks 😍. I love Arizona and all it’s natural beauty—and exploring it with a RZR is truly the best way to see it all 🏜#polarisadventures #offliner #sedonaatv

post7.caption: The most beautiful staircase by the sea 🌊 😍. Could you imagine having this in your backyard ?!

post8.caption: There’s nothing quite like the textures of the waves ✨🌊. I have been really unmotivated by Instagram for a long time. I shoot all the time but never share my work here because I get so caught up in the numbers and feeling disappointed if my work is not received well. I hate to admit that — but it’s true! And lately I’ve been trying not to be so self critical and just share because I love it. Might not happen over night, but I miss the community of this app 🤍. Thank you all for always being so kind to me ✨

post9.caption: Walking somewhere on the moon 🌙 👽. No but really—how is this place in the PNW ?! I haven’t ever seen anything like it 😍. Nature has made it’s own pyramids tucked away in Idaho of all places. Truly a natural wonder ✨
